body_html:
Ok, I found where the error is. It looks like that the Uint64 type is somehow unsupported when creating a 2D tensor using the Const operation (in the C library).

The error line is: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/go/operation_test.go#L126

If you comment these lines of code

		{ // Matrix of Uint64
			[][]uint64{
				{1, 2, 3},
				{4, 5, 6},
			},
			[]int64{2, 3},
			Uint64,
		},

go test works without raising SIGABRT.

Also, the error is about a "type 23", but from what I can see here (https://godoc.org/github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tensorflow/go#DataType ) there are only 22 data types available.

body:
Ok, I found where the error is. It looks like that the `Uint64` type is somehow unsupported when creating a 2D tensor using the `Const` operation (in the C library).

The error line is: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/go/operation_test.go#L126

If you comment these lines of code

```go
		{ // Matrix of Uint64
			[][]uint64{
				{1, 2, 3},
				{4, 5, 6},
			},
			[]int64{2, 3},
			Uint64,
		},
````

`go test` works without raising SIGABRT.

Also, the error is about a "type 23", but from what I can see here (https://godoc.org/github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tensorflow/go#DataType ) there are only 22 data types available.
